Reasonledger
============

Originator: Michael Patrick Aiello (ORCID 0009-0009-1429-9844)
Canonical repository: https://github.com/mpaiello/reasonledger
Archive / DOI: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19874728

Naming and lineage
------------------
Reasonledger is the standard developed and first documented under the name
AI-Native Notation (ANN). The earlier name is retained here so that the
authorship and priority record remains continuous across the rename.

Priority and disclosure
-----------------------
A US provisional patent application (63/980,973) was filed on 2026-02-12,
establishing an early, confidential priority record of the work. A provisional
application is not a public disclosure. The first public disclosure of the
specification was its publication in the project's canonical repository on
2026-04-28. This consolidated standard release is dated 2026-06-30.

The provisional application is being allowed to lapse. The public record
(repository history and archived deposit) establishes both authorship and the
priority of the disclosure, and serves as defensive publication so that the
format remains open to all and cannot be enclosed by a later third-party patent.

Open-standard terms
-------------------
Reasonledger is released as an open, royalty-free standard with no enforced
patent encumbrance. It is intended to be freely implementable by anyone,
including in commercial products.

  - Specification and documentation: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
    International (CC BY 4.0). See LICENSE.
  - Reference code: Apache License 2.0. See LICENSE-APACHE.

Development disclosure
----------------------
Reasonledger was developed through human-directed, AI-assisted work. The
specification and its validation were produced in collaboration with a large
language model (Claude, Anthropic). This is disclosed for transparency and does
not affect the terms above.

Not a blockchain
----------------
"Ledger" refers to the auditable record the format produces across a transfer
chain. Reasonledger involves no distributed ledger, token, chain, or consensus
mechanism of any kind.

